if SHIELD_BROWSER_BRIDGE

# The shield's gnss-nmea-generic node rides Zephyr's modem UART backend, which
# needs interrupt-driven (or async) reception. Both QEMU PL011s support the
# interrupt-driven API, so default it on whenever an app enables GNSS.
config UART_INTERRUPT_DRIVEN
	default y if GNSS

# Zephyr defaults to -Os. On AArch64 that is not merely a size/speed trade: it
# selects the toolchain's `space` multilib, whose picolibc compiles the hand
# written memcpy.S *out* and leaves only memcpy-stub.c — a byte-at-a-time loop
# costing six instructions per byte. Every one of those is emulated, so it is
# paid at wasm-JIT prices.
#
# It dominated the display path. Measured on qemu_cortex_a53 under the browser's
# own -icount shift=4, one 600x400 ARGB8888 frame through display_write():
#
#   -Os, byte-loop memcpy        92,337 us/frame     64x64 rect: 1,594 us
#   -O2, LDP/STP memcpy           2,625 us/frame     64x64 rect:    70 us
#
# ...a 35x difference on the copy that *is* the frame. It is not display
# specific — it is every memcpy the guest runs — so it belongs here, applied to
# every packaged image, rather than in one app's fragment. Costs ELF size, which
# these images can afford: they are fetched once and then interpreted forever.
# See docs/next-drivers.md, "virtio-gpu".
choice COMPILER_OPTIMIZATIONS
	default SPEED_OPTIMIZATIONS
endchoice

endif # SHIELD_BROWSER_BRIDGE
